Class AbstractGraph

  • java.lang.Object
    • AbstractGraph
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MyGraph
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MatrixGraph
    public abstract class AbstractGraph
extends java.lang.Object
implements MyGraph
    Abstract base class for MyGraphs. A MyGraph is a set of vertices and a set of edges. Vertices are represented by integers from 0 to n - 1. Edges are ordered pairs of vertices.

        public void loadEdgesFromFile​(java.util.Scanner scan)
                       throws java.io.IOException
        Load the edges of a MyGraph from the data in an input file. The file should contain a series of lines, each line with two or three data values. The first is the source, the second is the destination, and the optional third is the weight.
        Parameters:

        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if an I/O error occurs

      • createGraph

        public static MyGraph createGraph​(java.util.Scanner scan,
                                  boolean isDirected,
                                  java.lang.String type)
                           throws java.io.IOException
        Factory method to create a MyGraph and load the data from an input file. The first line of the input file should contain the number of vertices. The remaining lines should contain the edge data as described under loadEdgesFromFile.
        Parameters:
        scan - The Scanner connected to the data file
        isDirected - true if this is a directed MyGraph, false otherwise
        type - The string "Matrix" if an adjacency matrix is to be created
        Returns:
        a graph
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if type is not "Matrix"
        java.io.IOException - if file can not open
